INSERT INTO `resumes` VALUES (1,1,'/uploads/test_resume.pdf','Ahmed Raza - Software Engineer. 2 years experience in Python and Flask. Built REST APIs and database systems. Proficient in MySQL and React.','2026-05-08 07:00:41'),(2,2,'/uploads/ahmed_resume.pdf','Ahmed Raza - Full Stack Developer. Experience in Python, Flask, React, and MySQL. Built REST APIs and database-driven web apps.','2026-05-08 08:10:28'),(3,2,'uploads/CV Ahmed Raza.pdf','AHMED RAZA\nLanguages: C++ (Advanced), C, x86 Assembly (MASM/Irvine32), SQL, JavaScript.\nSystems: Manual Memory Management, Pointer Arithmetic, Stack Frame Analysis, CPU Register Optimization.\nTools/Math: Git, GDB, Raylib, SDL, Visual Studio, Linear Algebra, Probability and Statistics\nCoders Cup (2024, 2025): Solved complex algorithmic and data structure problems under high-pressure, timed\nconditions using C++. Ranked among the top performers at FAST-NUCES Karachi.\nDebug or Die: Traced and resolved critical logical errors and memory leaks in C++ codebases within strict time\nconstraints, demonstrating rapid system analysis.\nCode Roulette: Collaborated on team-based challenges involving high-performance SQL query analysis and C++\noptimization.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nTECHNICAL COMPETITIONS\nPROJECTS\nEmail: ahmedkazimx@gmail.com | Phone: +923325413136 | \nWordle Clone | x86 Assembly (MASM)\nDeveloped a bare-metal game using x86 Assembly, interfacing directly with CPU registers (EAX-EDX) and\nmemory addresses to manage state without high-level library overhead.\nOptimized register usage to minimize memory access cycles and implemented manual stack frames for\nprocedure calls.\nUtilized Irvine32 interrupts for hardware-level I/O.\nRV Rich Yet? | C++ & Raylib\nArchitected a modular C++ engine utilizing OOP to decouple the GUI layer from core logic, achieving O(1)\nquestion retrieval for trivia state management.\nManaged manual memory allocation and asset lifecycles in Raylib, ensuring zero memory leaks and stable\nperformance during extended sessions.\nOptimized the execution loop to handle asynchronous input without blocking the rendering thread.\nMaqsad Simulator | C & SDL Library\nEngineered a 2D engine in C using the SDL Library for low-level hardware abstraction of graphics/input.\nOptimized collision detection and sprite rendering via pointer arithmetic and direct memory manipulation.\nImplemented a fixed-time step game loop to ensure frame-rate independent physics and consistent execution.\nEDUCATION\nNational University of Computer and Emerging Sciences (FAST-NUCES) | Karachi, Pakistan Bachelor of Science in\nComputer Science | Expected June 2028\nCore Coursework: Data Structures & Algorithms, Computer Organization & Assembly Language (COAL), Linear\nAlgebra, Discrete Structures, Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), Probability and Statistics (In Progress),\nMultivariable Calculus\nLEADERSHIP AND VOLUNTEER EXPERIENCE\nSoftware Internship | Eden College: Optimized data processing for 100+ applicants using structured documentation,\nreducing data entry errors and improving system processing efficiency.\nLinkedIn | Github\nPROFILE SUMMARY\nSecond-year Computer Science student at FAST-NUCES Karachi with hands-on experience building performance-\nfocused software systems. Comfortable working close to the hardware level and solving problems that require both\nanalytical thinking and practical execution. Looking to apply a strong technical foundation in a real industry\nenvironment where I can contribute and grow.\n','2026-05-08 05:39:51'),(4,2,'uploads/CV Ahmed Raza.pdf','AHMED RAZA\nLanguages: C++ (Advanced), C, x86 Assembly (MASM/Irvine32), SQL, JavaScript.\nSystems: Manual Memory Management, Pointer Arithmetic, Stack Frame Analysis, CPU Register Optimization.\nTools/Math: Git, GDB, Raylib, SDL, Visual Studio, Linear Algebra, Probability and Statistics\nCoders Cup (2024, 2025): Solved complex algorithmic and data structure problems under high-pressure, timed\nconditions using C++. Ranked 