nnah University for courses containing Quantitative Research Methods, \nQuantitative Skills, Quality Management & Lean Six Sigma, Supply Chain Management, Strategic Supply Chain \nManagement, Transportation and Shipping Logistics, Operations Management, Statistical Inference, Probability & \nStatistical theories, Biostatistics, Business Statistics & Mathematics, Calculus, Differential Equations, Operations \nResearch, and Numerical Methods. Moreover, Dr. Shamsi is extensively involved in research activities and programs, \nhas written research papers on different statistical and management science projects and theories.  \nAt Mohammad Ali Jinnah University, currently Dr. Shamsi is heading School of Business Administration (SoBA), \nand apart from teaching and research, Dr. Shamsi served on various portfolios University-wide, Faculty-wide, and as \nwell as department-wide. Such as the General Co-Chair ICBM 2024, Conference Track Chair Supply Chain \nManagement, Focal Person of NBEAC, Coordinator of the Quality Enhancement Cell (QEC), Head of the Quality \nAssurance Committee (Management Science Department), Member of the Exam Vigilance Committee, Member of \nthe Canteen Committee, Member of the Students Affairs advisory team, Head of Business Administration Society \nand QEC representative in various Board of Faculties and Board of Studies meetings.  \n \nWORKING EXPERIENCE \n \nAssistant \nProfessor \nFeb 2018 – Present \nKarachi - Pakistan \n \nAt Mohammad Ali Jinnah University – MAJU \nAdministrative Positions: \n• \nHead of Department – School of Business Administration (September 2023 – \nPresent) \n• \nGeneral Co-Chair ICBM 2024 \n• \nConference Track Chair Supply Chain Management – ICBM 2024 \n• \nFocal Person NBEAC (2019- 2024) \n• \nQEC Representative of the Programs BBA, MBA, MS, Ph.D. (2019-2023) \n• \nHead, Quality Assurance Committee (Management Science Department) 2018-\n2019 \n• \nMember, Exam Vigilance Committee 2018-2019 \n• \nMember, Canteen Committee 2018-2019 \nTeaching Positions: \nFeb 2018- onwards \n• \nAssistant Professor, Faculty of Business Administration (FoBA)  \nDescription:    \n- \nActively involved in graduate and undergraduate levels of teaching. \no \nTaught Advanced Research Methodology to MBA and MS Students \no \nTaught Quantitative Research Methods to MS Management Science \no \nTaught Statistical Inference to MBA and BBA Programs \no \nTaught Probability & Statistics to BSCS Program \no \nTaught Quality Management & Lean Six Sigma to MBA Program \nP a g e  | 2 \no \nTaught Supply Chain Management to BBA and MBA Program \no \nTaught Strategic Supply Chain Management to MBA Program. \no \nTaught Transport and Shipping Logistics to MBA Program. \no \nTaught Business Statistics and Business Mathematics to BBA & MBA \nProgram \n- \nAssessment of students’ coursework through quizzes, exams, and presentations.  \n- \nSupervising students’ research projects and theses at undergraduate, graduate and \nPhD levels.  \n- \nFocal Person of NBEAC \no \nResponsible for NBEAC accreditation of Faculty of Business \nAdministration and Social Sciences programs (MBA and BBA) \no \nSuccessfully conducted NBEAC visit and got accredited MBA and BBA \nprograms under X Category (3 years of accreditation). \n- \nInvolved in Quality Enhancement Cell as a QEC representative \no \nAligned operations, activities, and policies for compliance with HEC \nguidelines. \no \nPrepared and submitted University Portfolio Report along with the detailed \nStatistics and Self-Assessment Report (SARs) to HEC \no \nConducted a successful external IPE 2018 \n▪ \nAccomplished with a satisfactory evaluation of the Institutional \nPerformance Evaluation (IPE) visit of HEC representatives. \n▪ \nImplemented Compliance Implementation Plan (CIP) as feedback \nof shortcomings after IPE visit. \no \nConducted a successful CIEC visit in 2019. \n▪ \nPrepared SARs for Charter Inspection & Evaluation Committee \n(CIEC-HEC) visit \n▪ \nAccomplished with a satisfactory evaluation of the Charter \nInspection & Evaluation Committee (CIEC) visit of HEC \nrepresentatives. \no \nAttended BOS, BOF, BASR, and BOI meetings as QEC Representative \n- \nInvolved in Exam Vigilance Committee \no \nMember of Exam vigilance committee and performed Mid and Final exam \nvigilance for all MAJU during Spring 2019 and prepared a detailed report \nof vigilance. \n- \nInvolved in the Management Science Society as Society Chairman during 2018 \nLecturer \nSep 2016 – Feb 2018 \nKarachi - Pakistan \n \nAt Shaheed Zulfikar Ali Bhutto Institute of Science & Technology-SZABIST \nDescription:    \n- \nActed as the Head of the Mathematics and Statistics Cluster \no \nAttended BOS meetings \n- \nActively involved in graduate and undergraduate levels of teaching. \no \nTeaching Statistical Inference to BBA and BABS programs in Fall 2017 \no \nTaught SMB (Statistics and Mathematics) to BABS and Operations \nManagement in the BBA program in the Spring of 2017. \nP a g e  | 3 \no \nTaught Business Statistics to BBA, Statistical Inference to MBA & BABS, \nand Quantitative Tools for Managers to MBA evening students in the \nsemester Fall 2016 \n- \nActively involved in the accreditation process of SZABIST with CILT-UK \n- \nOrganized a Conference on Accelerated Corporate Excellence on the theme of \nKAIZEN Beyond Auto Industry in Spring 2017 \nLecturer \nFeb 2007 – Aug 2016 \nKarachi - Pakistan \n \nAt the National University of Computer & Emerging Sciences- FAST \nDescription:    \n- \nActed as the In-Charge Department of Sciences and Humanities and looked after all \nthe matters related to faculty and departments, including the faculty \nrecruitment/hiring process. \n- \nActed as the Chair of Mathematics and Statistics faculty members and cross-\nvalidated the question papers of Mathematics and Statistics as a Moderator. \n- \nActed as the Chair Cafeteria Committee and look after all the matters related to \nFAST Cafeteria. \n- \nActively involved in graduate/undergraduate levels of teaching. \n- \nInvolved in matters related to QEC (quality enhancement cell). \n- \nTaught various courses to departments of Computer Sciences, Management \nSciences, and Electrical Engineering which mainly includes Statistical theories, \nmethods & research areas. \n- \nSome of the main courses are  \n▪ \nBusiness Statistics & Mathematics        Probability and Random Processes \n▪ \nProbability and Statistics                       Applied Calculus \n▪ \nNumerical Methods                               Operations Research \n▪ \nPrincipal of Economics                         Differential Equations \n▪ \nStatistical Inference                               Quantitative Techniques in Analysis \n- \nPartially involved in teaching Master level students (MS-SPM, MS-CS, and MBA) \nand mentoring them about “Empirical Research Methods”, to explore different \ndimensions of research in computer sciences and businesses through SPSS. \n- \nDesign & distribute statistical assignments reports to students each semester as per \nprovided procedure & schedule. \n- \nKeeping a record of every concerned student’s activity and short-term results \n- \nProviding support and coordination to the department seniors for preparation of \nexams and upcoming activities \nAggressively taking part in departmental seminars, and events & demonstrate \nprovided updates & programmed material when required \nCooperative \nLecturer \nJan 2005 - Jan 2007 \nKarachi - Pakistan \n \nAt the University of Karachi – Department of Statistics \nDescription:    \n- \nMost actively involved in taking subsidiary classes for undergraduate students to \ndifferent departments.; Subjects Include:  \n▪ \nElementary Statistics I and II, Probability Theory I and II, Biostatistics I \nand II  \nP a g e  | 4 \n- \nTaught the “Quantitative Analysis in Research” program through Minitab and \nSPSS software to the students of MSc – Applied Statistics. The main objective of \nQAR is to