ience) \nMatric Board \n \nPUBLICATIONS \nInternational Journal: \n▪ \nIbrahim, M., Mahmood, R. & Som, H.M. Green absorptive capacity and environmental performance: a \nperspective of SMEs’ relational capability and green supply chain management practices. Environ Dev Sustain \n(2024). https://doi.org/10.1007/s10668-023-04420-5 (Scopus, IF=4.9, HEC W) \n▪ \nIbrahim, M., & Mahmood, R. (2022), “Proactive Environmental Strategy and Environmental Performance of \nthe Manufacturing SMEs of Karachi City in Pakistan: Role of Green Mindfulness as a DCV”, Sustainability, \n14(19), 12431. (Scopus, IF=3.9, HEC W) \n▪ \nAziz Saifee, A. G. Baloch, Irfan Khalid and M. Ibrahim Shamsi, (2012) “A Survey on the Progress of Arabic \nLanguage Teaching in Madarsa Educational Board (Wifaq-ul-Madaris Al-Arabia Pakistan)” European Journal \nof Social Sciences ISSN 1450-2267 Vol.31 No.4, pp. 558-566 \n \nP a g e  | 5 \nNational Journal:  \n▪ \nM. Ibrahim Shamsi and Shahnawaz A. S. (2015) “A Study of the Logistics Capability Factors for an E-\ncommerce Market” FAST-NU Research Journal, ISSN: 2313-7045, Vol 1, No. 2, pp. 143-149 \n▪ \nM. Ibrahim Shamsi and G. Hussain, (2007) \"Bootstrap Confidence Interval for Parameter \'p\' of Truncated \nNegative Binomial Distribution\" Journal of Management and Social Sciences, Vol.3, No. 2, 77-86 \n \nInternational Conference: \n▪ \nAdila, Suffah A., M. Ibrahim Shamsi, (2016) “The Impact of Logistics Support on Building Trust in Online \nShopping” Proc. 14th International Conference on Statistical Sciences Karachi, March 14-16, 2016, Vol. 29, pp. \n355-362. \n▪ \nMeghna J., S. Mahrukh, M. Ibrahim Shamsi, (2016) “The Effects of Illiteracy as a Main Cause of Corruption” \nProc. 14th International Conference on Statistical Sciences Karachi, March 14-16, 2016, Vol. 29, pp. 347-354. \n▪ \nHammad W., M. Ibrahim Shamsi, Sadiq A., Zohaib A., and Rafique A., (2016) “Effectiveness of Leadership \nStyle on Employee Performance” Proc. 14th International Conference on Statistical Sciences Karachi, March \n14-16, 2016, Vol. 29, pp. 335-346. \n▪ \nM. Ibrahim Shamsi, S. Taha, and A. Uzair, (2014) “On Firm Performance the Effect of Span of Supply Chain \nIntegration” Proc. 12th International Conference on Statistical Sciences Karachi, March 24-26, 2014, Vol. 26, \npp. 491-500. \n▪ \nM. Ibrahim Shamsi, Shuja Hasan, and Salman Samad, (2014) “University Branding, its Effect on Industry for \nFresh Graduated Student’s Job Placement” Proc. 12th International Conference on Statistical Sciences Karachi, \nMarch 24-26, 2014, Vol. 26, pp. 457-464.  \n▪ \nM. Ibrahim Shamsi, M. Haris Abdullah, and Farhal Naseem, (2014) “The Impact of After-sale Services on \nConsumer Buying Behavior in Broad Band Industry of Karachi” Proc. 12th International Conference on \nStatistical Sciences Karachi, March 24-26, 2014, Vol. 26, pp. 219-228. \n▪ \nM. Ibrahim Shamsi, G. Hussain, (2008) “Wild Bootstrap Technique for Finding Confidence Interval of \nTruncated Negative Binomial Parameter ‘p’” Proceeding 4th International Statistical Conference, Gujrat, Vol. \n16, Pages 133 – 142. \nNational Conference: \n▪ \nS. Fatima, G. Hussain and M. Ibrahim Shamsi, (2007) “Bayesian Dynamic Linear, Artificial Neural Network \nand ARIMA models for quarterly GDP at market price” Proceeding 3rd National Statistical Conference, \nLahore, Vol. 14, Pages 331 – 336. \n \nCERTIFICATION & EXTERNAL COLLABORATION PROGRAMS: \n1. 7th DD Conference 2020 at HEC Islamabad \nAwarded a certificate of participation by National Business Education Accreditation Council (NBEAC) chairman \nDr. Farrukh Iqbal in recognition of attending “Enhancing Quality and Inclusivity in Business Education through \nEngagement”  \n \n \n \n \n \n \n    Held on February 17 – 18, 2020, in Islamabad \n \n2. Bloom’s Taxonomy at Work – HEC VCON \nOrganized and attended a video conferencing workshop on the topic “Putting Bloom’s Taxonomy at Work” \ndelivered by Dr. Qaiser Munir at IBA Karachi virtually connected at MAJU \n \n \n \n \n \n \n    Held on March 27th, 2019, MAJU Karachi \n \n3. Skill Building and Enhancement Workshop “Emotional Intelligence” \nAttended one day workshop on Skill building and Enhancement through Emotional Intelligence organized by MAJU \ntalked by Prof Dr. Ameena Zehra, Department of Psychology, University of Karachi \n \n \n \n \n \n \n     Held on March 22nd, 2019, MAJU Karachi \nP a g e  | 6 \n \n4. Quality Design in Business Management Program (QDBMP) \nAttended one day Workshop on Designing Quality in Business Management Programs and Embedding Future \nSkills in the Program’s Strategic Plan organized by QEC of the Institute of Business Management, Karachi \n \n \n \n \n \n \n     Held on Oct 18th, 2018, IoBM, Karachi \n \n \n5. Executive Breakfast (CELDD) \nAttended a Workshop on Four Decades of Real Estate in Karachi (1980 to 2018) organized by Mohammad Ali \nJinnah University CELDD, Karachi \n \n \n \n \n \n \n     Held on Aug 31st, 2018, MAJU, Karachi \n \n6. E-Learning Capacity Building Workshop (MOODLE) \nAttended a Workshop on E-Learning Capacity Building Workshop: Be a Competitive Teacher with the help of \nMOODLE organized by Mohammad Ali Jinnah QEC, Karachi \n \n \n \n \n \n \n     Held on May 17th, 2018, at MAJU, Karachi \n \n7. 2nd NRCMB at SZABIST \nOrganized the 2nd National Research Conference on Management and Business (NRCMB) on the theme of Building \nBridges between Industry and Academia  \n \n                                                   Held on November 24-25, 2017 at SZABIST 90, Karachi \n \n8. 2nd International CPEC Business and Research Conference (ICPEC-BRC2) \nAttended the 2-days conference on China-Pakistan Economic Corridor – An Opportunity for Economics and Social \nTransformation organized by IBA Karachi in partnership with SILC Business School, Shanghai University, China \n \n \n \n \n \n \n     Held on March 15th and 16th, 2017, IBA, Karachi  \n \n9. 14th International Conference on Statistical Sciences (ICSS-14) \nAttended ICSS 14 at Jinnah Sindh Medical University Karachi organized by ISOSS and presented 3 research papers  \n       Held on March 2016, JSMU, Karachi  \n \n10. 12th International Conference on Statistical Sciences (ICSS-12) \nAttended ICSS 12 at DOW University Karachi organized by ISOSS and presented 3 research papers  \n       Held on March 2014, DUHS, Karachi  \n \n11. Colloquium on “BIG DATA Innovation” (BDI) \nAttended 8th Annual Mathematics Colloquium on “BIG DATA Innovation” as a guest organized by IoBM  \n \n \n \n \n \n \n      Held on Feb 2014, CBM, Karachi \n \n \n12.  Postgraduate Research Tools- Research Made Easy (RME-SPSS) \nAttended HD video conference an international research workshop  \n     Organized on 29-30 Jan 2014, FAST Karachi  \n13. Participation in a workshop: “Writing Research Paper” \nJointly organized by Applied Economics Research Center (AERC) & Institute of Research Promotion (IRP) \nHeld on 16th April 2010 at AERC, University of Karachi \n14. Staff Development Program (TASK)  \nAttended 26 days program organized by the Department of Genetics, University of Karachi, and the Higher \nEducation Commission of Pakistan (HEC). \n    Held on Dec 2006 to Jan 2007 at Genetics Dept., KU   \n15. Total Quality Management (TQM) ISO9000-2001 \nAttended and certified TQM, organized by the Department of Statistics, University of Karachi collaboration with \nLakson Group of Companies from January 2004 to December 2004. \nHeld on Jan 2004 to Dec 2004 at Statistics Dept., KU   \n','2026-05-09 06:55:13'),(20,4,'uploads/Laiba Jamil.pdf','Laiba Jamil \nKarachi, Pakistan \n+92 336 131 2347 | laibajamil2007@gmail.com  \n \nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY \nMotivated Computer Science undergraduate at FAST-NUCES with a strong foundation in \nprogramming, object-oriented design, data structures, and databases. Hands-on experience \nbuilding academic software projects in C++, Python, SQL, and web technologies. Strong \nproblem-solving mindset with interest in software engineering, backend development, and AI-\ndriven systems. Seeking internship opportunities to apply technical skills in a professional \nenvironment. \n \nEDUCATION \nFAST-NUCES, Karachi \nBachelor of Science in Computer Science | 2024 – Present \nCGPA: 3.52 / 4.00 \nRelevant Coursework: \nData Structures & Algorithms, OOP, Database Systems, Operating Systems, Artificial \nIntelligence \nKhatoon – e - Pakistan, Karachi \nIntermediate (Pre-Engineering) | 2022 – 2024 \nThe Crescent Academy \nMatric (Computer Science) | Completed 2022 \n \nTECHNICAL SKILLS \nLanguages: C++, Python, SQL, C, HTML, CSS, Assembly Language \nConcepts: OOP, Data Structures, DBMS, Algorithms, Problem Solving \nTools: Visual Studio Code, Oracle SQL, Ubuntu, Git (Basic) \nSoft Skills: Communication, Teamwork, Analytical Thinking, Time Management \n \nPROJECTS \nPacman Game | C++ / Raylib \n \nDeveloped a graphical Pac-Man game with player movement, ghost logic, and collision \ndetection. \n \nApplied object-oriented design principles for modular gameplay components. \n \nManaged game states, scoring system, and movement algorithms. \nRide Booking System | C++ \n \nBuilt a console-based ride booking system using OOP concepts. \n \nImplemented ride scheduling, fare calculation, and booking workflows. \n \nDesigned scalable modular classes for users and rides. \n4-Way Traffic Control System | Logisim \n \nDesigned an FSM-based traffic light controller with pedestrian crossing support. \n \nImplemented timer-based transitions using sequential and combinational logic. \nClothing Store Website | HTML / CSS \n \nCreated a responsive front-end e-commerce website UI. \n \nFocused on clean navigation, structured layouts, and user-friendly design. \nHangman Game | C \n \nBuilt a text-based game using loops, arrays, strings, and conditionals. \nTic-Tac-Toe Game | Assembly Language \n \nDeveloped a complete low-level game using registers, memory handling, and control \nflow. \n \nEXPERIENCE \nPrivate Tutor | Self-Employed | Karachi \n2024 – Present \n \nTaught students academic subjects through one-on-one sessions. \n \nSimplified technical and mathematical concepts for better understanding. \n \nManaged scheduling, planning, and communication independently. \n \nEXTRA INFORMATION \n \nStrong interest in Software Development and AI Applications \n \nQuick learner with collaborative mindset \n \nAvailable for internships and entry-level opportunities \n \n','2026-05-09 06:56:17'),(21,4,'uploads/Laiba Jamil.pdf','Laiba Jamil \nKarachi, Pakistan \n+92 336 131 2347 | laibajamil2007@gmail.com  \n \nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY \nMotivated Computer Science undergraduate at FAST-NUCES with a strong foundation in \nprogramming, object-oriented design, data structures, and databases. Hands-on experience \nbuilding academic software projects in C++, Python, SQL, and web technologies. Strong \nproblem-solving mindset with interest in software engineering, backend development, and AI-\ndriven systems. Seeking internship opportunities to apply technical skills in a professional \nenvironment. \n \nEDUCATION \nFAST-NUCES, Karachi \nBachelor of Science in Computer Science | 2024 – Present \nCGPA: 3.52 / 4.00 \nRelevant Coursework: \nData Structures & Algorithms, OOP, Database Systems, Operating Systems, Artificial \nIntelligence \nKhatoon – e - Pakistan, Karachi \nIntermediate (Pre-Engineering) | 2022 – 2024 \nThe Crescent Academy \nMatric (Computer Science) | Completed 2022 \n \nTECHNICAL SKILLS \nLanguages: C++, Python, SQL, C, HTML, CSS, Assembly Language \nConcepts: OOP, Data Structures, DBMS, Algorithms, Problem Solving \nTools: Visual Studio Code, Oracle SQL, Ubuntu, Git (Basic) \nSoft Skills: Communication, Teamwork, Analytical Thinking, Time Management \n \nPROJECTS \nPacman Game | C++ / Raylib \n \nDeveloped a graphical Pac-Man game with player movement, ghost logic, and collision \ndetection. \n \nApplied object-oriented design principles for modular gameplay components. \n \nManaged game states, scoring system, and movement algorithms. \nRide Booking System | C++ \n \nBuilt a console-based ride booking system using OOP concepts. \n \nImplemented ride scheduling, fare calculation, and booking workflows. \n \nDesigned scalable modular classes for users and rides. \n4-Way Traffic Control System | Logisim \n \nDesigned an FSM-based traffic light controller with pedestrian crossing support. \n \nImplemented timer-based transitions using sequential and combinational logic. \nClothing Store Website | HTML / CSS \n \nCreated a responsive front-end e-commerce website UI. \n \nFocused on clean navigation, structured layouts, and user-friendly design. \nHangman Game | C \n \nBuilt a text-based game using loops, arrays, strings, and conditionals. \nTic-Tac-Toe Game | Assembly Language \n \nDeveloped a complete low-level game using registers, memory handling, and control \nflow. \n \nEXPERIENCE \nPrivate Tutor | Self-Employed | Karachi \n2024 – Present \n \nTaught students academic subjects through one-on-one sessions. \n \nSimplified technical and mathematical concepts for better understanding. \n \nManaged scheduling, planning, and communication independently. \n \nEXTRA INFORMATION \n \nStrong interest in Software Development and AI Applications \n \nQuick learner with collaborative mindset \n \nAvailable for internships and entry-level opportunities \n \n','2026-05-09 06:59:33');
